* - selects all elements
type selector --> h1 { css code} --> selects all h1 in the document

class selector --> .<classname> {css} - selects all elements with the selected class name

id selector --> #<id> {css} --> selects the element(one) with the selected id

attribute selector --> [attr] or [attr=value] [attr~=value] ...
[attr] -- all element that have this attribute (any value)
[attr=value] - all elements with value equal to value

List selectors 
selectorA,(with comma) selectorB {css} - selects elements with both selectors

Comninator selectors
with space - selects all descendants of the first selector
selectorA <--(space)selectorB {css} 
article image {css} --> will select all image tegs with parents article tag

child selector
A > B {css} - selects all Bs with parent A
#id > p {css } --> will select all <p>s in the parent with the selected id

siblings selector
A ~ B {css}
B element that follows A element ( not needed immediately)
p ~ span {css}

direct sibling
A + B {css}
B element that  IMMEDIATELY follows A element
just the first element!!!!  
p + span {css}

For additional -- see Mozilla docs Peseudo selectors and so on 
pseudo:
p:last-of-type --> in all tags the last <p>




